HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 922
By Haston
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Libby Bromley of
Hardin County High School on finishing as a
finalist in the TSSAA Division I girls' individual
bowling state championship tournament.
WHEREAS, we take great pleasure in recognizing those dedicated student athletes who
serve as the heart and soul of their schools and communities while excelling in competition; and
WHEREAS, one such outstanding individual is Libby Bromley of Hardin County High
School, who recently finished as a finalist in the TSSAA Division I girls' individual bowling state
championship tournament; and
WHEREAS, recording 1,214 pins and a 202.3 average in the semi-final round, Ms.
Bromley bested forty-seven bowlers to finish first and advance to the state championship match;
and
WHEREAS, Libby Bromley epitomizes all that is good in today's student athlete, as she
has achieved a premier level of success in competition while exhibiting the highest degree of
character in all aspects of life; and
WHEREAS, the perseverance, determination, work ethic, and talent of this young
woman not only made possible a championship season but also surely bode well for her future
success; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Bromley has distinguished herself as a dominant bowler of whom we
can all be proud, and she is most worthy of our approbation at this time; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Libby Bromley of Hardin County High School
